I"<p>The <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/memetic-psychotherapy-is-like-an-ophtalmologist-not-a-painter">view</a> of the <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/world-models-reflect-ideological-structures">world</a> as a collaborator, something which helps you learn and develop, might be a pragmatic <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/affect-reflects-ideological-structures">paradigm</a>. Ups can be <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/memetic-psychotherapy-equips-prefrontal-areas-with-mental-tools-for-managing-limbic-friction">framed</a> as celebrated success in <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/interpersonal-backlinks-incentivize-collaborative-knowledge-work">collaboration</a>, while downs can be seen as impersonal unintentional limitations.</p>
